<h4 id="1-metacharacters">1. Metacharacters</h4>

<ol>
  <li>Unix shell provides various metacharacters which have special meaning while
using them in any shell script.
    <div class="language-shell highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><span class="k">*</span> ? <span class="o">[]</span> <span class="s1">' " \ $ ; &amp; ( ) | ^ &lt; &gt; space tab
</span></code></pre></div>    </div>
  </li>
</ol>

<h4 id="2-quoting-mechanisme">2. Quoting Mechanisme</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Single quote: All special characters between these quotes lost their special
meaning</li>
  <li>Double quote: Most special characters between these quotes lost their special
meaning with some exceptions</li>
  <li>Any character immediately following the backslash loses its special meaning.</li>
  <li>Anything in between back quotes would be treated as a command and would be
executed.</li>
</ol>

